Speech Recognition Program with ASCII Art Output
This Python program utilizes speech recognition and displays the recognized text in a large font format using ASCII art. It leverages the pyttsx3 text-to-speech engine, the speech_recognition module to capture audio and recognize speech, and pyfiglet to display the recognized text in the terminal as ASCII art.

Features:
Speech Recognition: Captures and processes speech through your microphone.
Noise Reduction: Automatically adjusts for ambient noise to enhance the accuracy of speech recognition.
Large Text Display: Converts the recognized text into a large, eye-catching ASCII art format for terminal display.
Prerequisites:
Before running this program, make sure you have the following libraries installed:

pyttsx3: A text-to-speech conversion library in Python.
speech_recognition: A library that provides functionality to convert speech to text.
pyfiglet: A module that enables ASCII art text rendering in the terminal.
Installation
You can install the required libraries using pip:

bash
Copy code
pip install pyttsx3 SpeechRecognition pyfiglet
Usage
Run the Program: The program listens to your voice input via the microphone.
Speech Recognition: The recognized text is displayed on the terminal.
Error Handling: If the program doesn't understand the spoken words or faces an issue, appropriate error messages are shown in large ASCII text format.
